<p>LIE DOWN</p>
<p>cubare refers to animate beings not standing up but lying down, typically in order to recuperate his strength.</p>
<p>situm esse refers to inanimate objects lying in a position with no special reference to whether they lie flat rather than standing upright.</p>
<p>jacere refers to the jacent position of animate or inanimate things.</p>
